'''Gay Robins''' is an art historian. She was formerly the [[Samuel Candler Dobbs]] Professor of Art History at [[Emory University]]. She now holds the title of professor emerita. She also assisted the [[Michael C. Carlos Museum]] as a faculty consultant for [[Ancient Egyptian Art]].<ref name=":0">{{cite web|title=Gay Robins|url=http://arthistory.emory.edu/home/people/faculty/robins.html|website=arthistory.emory.edu|publisher=Emory University|accessdate=8 March 2017|language=en}}</ref> Her work focuses on [[ancient Egyptian art]], [[Composition (visual arts)|composition]], [[gender]] and [[sexuality]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.livescience.com/28510-hatshepsut-first-female-pharaoh.html|title=Hatshepsut: First Female Pharaoh|last=Jarus|first=Owen|date=April 5, 2013|work=Live Science|access-date=2017-03-08|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=}}</ref>
